OL,7,FLeaving aside the matter of the
OL,8,Frecession at the end of last year
OL,9,F(which may yet be revised away), the
OL,10,Foutlook for economic growth is not
OL,11,Fgreat.
OL,13,FInterest rates have risen sharply,
OL,14,Fwhich means the government is now
OL,15,Fspending a lot more to service its
OL,16,Fdebt.
OL,18,FAnd that debt is set to continue
OL,19,Frising, stabilising only in five years
OL,20,Ftime, despite the government's pledge
OL,21,Fto bring it down.
