OL,7,FThe tax burden has risen dramatically
OL,8,Fsince 2018.
OL,10,FThe "state" has got bigger but there
OL,11,Fare plenty of signs that public
OL,12,Fservices are really struggling in
OL,13,Fplaces - partly because of the
OL,14,Fpressure the pandemic put on them,
OL,15,Fpartly because the population is
OL,16,Fgrowing and people are living longer.
OL,18,FIn summary, and as Liam Byrne might
OL,19,Fput it, "there's no money left."
