OL,7,F"Headroom" is probably best thought of
OL,8,Fas the amount of money by which the
OL,9,Fchancellor could cut taxes or raise
OL,10,Fspending and still meet his fiscal
OL,11,Ftargets for borrowing and debt in five
OL,12,Fyears time.
OL,14,FAccording to Treasury sources, the
OL,15,FOffice For Budget Responsibility (OBR)
OL,16,Ftold the chancellor last week that he
OL,17,Fwas on course to meet his primary
OL,18,Ffiscal rule - for public sector net
OL,19,Fdebt to fall in the final year of its
OL,20,Fforecast (2028/29) - by a margin of
OL,21,Faround #13 billion.
