OL,7,FIndividually, none of the above would
OL,8,Fbe a big money-spinner for the
OL,9,FTreasury. Even collectively they are
OL,10,Funlikely to raise anything like #14
OL,11,Fbillion.
OL,13,FWhat will tax cuts mean for public
OL,14,Fservices?
OL,16,FCutting national insurance should
OL,17,Fstimulate economic activity but tax
OL,18,Fcuts rarely pay for themselves.
OL,20,FIn general, lower taxes require lower
OL,21,Fgovernment spending in the long run.
