OL,7,FElsewhere in the public sector,
OL,8,Fprisons are running out of space; the
OL,9,Fcourts are clogged with cases; the
OL,10,Fpolice are struggling to respond to
OL,11,Fburglaries, schools have recruitment
OL,12,Fdifficulties and universities are
OL,13,Fwrestling with a fall in international
OL,14,Fstudents (whose fees subsidise those
OL,15,Fof UK students).
OL,17,FIn his Autumn Statement last November,
OL,18,Fyou may recall the chancellor used the
OL,19,Fhigher tax revenues that high
OL,20,Finflation has generated to fund a
OL,21,Fchunky tax cut to national insurance.
