OL,7,FIn January, the head of the OBR, the
OL,8,FTreasury's independent forecaster,
OL,9,Ftold a Lords committee that the lack
OL,10,Fof detail about the government's
OL,11,Ffuture spending plans meant its
OL,12,Fforecasts on the outlook for the
OL,13,Fpublic finances were beyond "a work of
OL,14,Ffiction".
OL,16,FRichard Hughes complained "the
OL,17,Fgovernment hasn't even bothered to
OL,18,Fwrite down what its departmental
OL,19,Fspending plan are, underpinning the
OL,20,Fplan for public services".
