OL,4,Cquestions answered ahead of Hunt's
OL,5,CBudget
OL,7,FThe risk is that cutting taxes may
OL,8,Fmean interest rates fall less quickly
OL,9,Fthan they otherwise would.
OL,11,FOf course, it could be that the tax
OL,12,Fcuts in the Budget are balanced out
OL,13,Fwith tax rises elsewhere and that
OL,14,Foverall there's no significant
OL,15,Finjection of cash into the economy.
OL,17,FBut then the chancellor would be
OL,18,Fcreating losers as well as winners. He
OL,19,Fcan't have it both ways.
OL,21,FDo the fiscal rules need changing?
