OL,7,FThe chancellor has his eyes fixed on a
OL,8,Fgeneral election.
OL,10,FHe will present his Budget as an
OL,11,Fattempt to revive our economic
OL,12,Fprospects but he is also hoping it
OL,13,Fwill prove a vote-winner.
OL,15,FIn a few months time the public will
OL,16,Fbe asked to choose the next government.
OL,18,FAs it stands, the economic strategies
OL,19,Fof the Conservatives and Labour look
OL,20,Fvery similar.
